{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1772136910,"nonce":"gvHOZ9hzJuaXPelSfCM+qeZR8v0=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87uRctN","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/293","origin":"github"},"title":"Document env.sh requirement for per-package testing","message":"## Problem\n\nThe Build \u0026 Test section in `AGENTS.md` and the Testing section in `.agent/knowledge/ros2_development_patterns.md` show `colcon test` and `colcon test-result` as standalone commands:\n\n```bash\ncolcon test --packages-select \u003cpackage\u003e\ncolcon test-result --verbose\n```\n\nAI agents execute each command in an isolated subprocess (fresh shell) — this applies to Claude Code, Gemini CLI, and GitHub Copilot agents alike. Without `env.sh` sourced in the same shell, `colcon test` fails with `ModuleNotFoundError: No module named 'ament_cmake_test'` because the ROS 2 base and workspace overlay environments aren't loaded.\n\nAgents consistently struggle with this, wasting multiple attempts before discovering they need to chain environment sourcing with the test command.\n\n## Proposed Fix\n\n1. **`AGENTS.md` Build \u0026 Test section**: Show per-package testing as a single chained command that sources `env.sh` first, and mention `make test` for full workspace runs.\n\n2. **`.agent/knowledge/ros2_development_patterns.md` Testing section**: Same — add environment sourcing to the test commands and note that `make test` handles this automatically.\n\nExample pattern:\n```bash\n# Per-package testing (env.sh must be sourced in the same shell)\nsource .agent/scripts/env.sh \u0026\u0026 cd layers/main/\u003clayer\u003e_ws \u0026\u0026 \\\n  colcon test --packages-select \u003cpackage\u003e \u0026\u0026 colcon test-result --verbose\n```\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null}]}